ects and varieties encountered. The purpose of the present volume is to complement and enrich the existing studies by providing readers with a kaleidoscopic perspective, allowing for a holistic interpretation and understanding of Northern English. It includes studies not only on phonology but also on semantics, syntax and sociolinguistics from a synchronic and diachronic point of view, with a special emphasis on the process of enregisterment. The varieties covered include Scottish Standard English, Shetland and Northern Ireland as well as varieties from the North of England.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aEnglish languagexDialectszEngland, NorthernvCongresses. 0aEnglish languagexVariationzEngland, NorthernvCongresses. 4aDialektologie. 4aGeneral Linguistics. 4aNorthern Englishes. 4aSprache / English. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBeal, Joan C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHancil, Sylvie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104487400 cprintz978311044865840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045090340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110450903423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110450903.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_E